Grammar research

Before the subject can start learning on its own, we need to create a medium/context in which new things learned can be stated.
To do this, I propose building up a concept web of definitions and simple facts through English conversation. We first teach the basic rules
of grammar. It is okay to teach these to the learner because they are arbitrary and unlikely to be gleaned without help.

Words can be slightly modified to indicate their grammatical use. We should cluster these together into word categories defined by the root word.



A sentence, as I understand it, is made up of clauses. A clause contains a subject and predicate, and the predicate is usually either a lone
verb, or a verb together with another object to which the verb is relating the subject.

For starters, we'll use simple sentences


